OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F367A1779196276
OL,3,CConcerns around local election vote
OL,4,Ccounting process to be investigated
OL,6,FThree candidates' vote totals were
OL,7,Finitially declared incorrectly, with
OL,8,Fone Liberal Democrat candidate
OL,9,Factually receiving 751 fewer votes
OL,10,Fthan originally stated.
OL,12,FLiberal Democrat Andrew Menzies
OL,13,Finitially declared to have 946 votes
OL,14,Fhad actually received 195.
OL,16,FThe Green Party's Teddy Morgan
OL,17,Finitially declared to have 90 votes
OL,18,Fhad actually received 540.
OL,1,Woz5~k4{$z%~s1z5jw=hw1         G2/6
OL,2,W,.!+.!/*%/*%,.!/*%/*%/"-$T,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BYorks News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,368,360,260,120,000,100
PN,36703
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F367A1779196276
OL,3,CConcerns around local election vote
OL,4,Ccounting process to be investigated
OL,6,FWhile Conservative Chris Pillai
OL,7,Finitially declared to have 659 votes
OL,8,Fhad actually received 960.
OL,10,FLabour candidate for Rastrick Peter
OL,11,FJudge has stopped short of asking for
OL,12,Fa re-run but has asked the Council's
OL,13,Fchief executive Robin Tuddenham to
OL,14,Frespond to his concerns about how the
OL,15,FRastrick vote was handled, saying he
OL,16,Fwas not satisfied with how issues he
OL,17,Fraised on the night were addressed at
OL,18,Fthe time.
OL,1,Woz5~k4{$z%~s1z5jw=hw1         G3/6
OL,2,W,.!+.!/*%/*%,.!/*%/*%/"-$T,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BYorks News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,368,360,260,120,000,100
PN,36704
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F367A1779196276
OL,3,CConcerns around local election vote
OL,4,Ccounting process to be investigated
OL,6,FMr Judge questioned whether the
OL,7,Fprocess was satisfactory and wants the
OL,8,Fcouncil to ask the Electoral
OL,9,FCommission (EC) for its views.
OL,11,FResponding to Mr Judge's concerns, Mr
OL,12,FTuddenham said: "This complaint
OL,13,Findicates no desire to challenge the
OL,14,Foutcome of the election in the ward,
OL,15,Fand the election of the three
OL,16,Fcouncillors for this ward in
OL,17,FCalderdale, which is clear and
OL,18,Fdefinitive.
OL,1,Woz5~k4{$z%~s1z5jw=hw1         G4/6
OL,2,W,.!+.!/*%/*%,.!/*%/*%/"-$T,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BYorks News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,368,360,260,120,000,100
PN,36705
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F367A1779196276
OL,3,CConcerns around local election vote
OL,4,Ccounting process to be investigated
OL,6,F"I can advise that there was an
OL,7,Fadministrative error in the
OL,8,Fcalculation relating to the votes for
OL,9,Fthree candidates.
OL,11,F"This was identified, and after a
OL,12,Freview, I declared the corrected
OL,13,Fposition at the count.
OL,15,F"I have written to Mr Judge advising
OL,16,Fhim that I will investigate the
OL,17,Fvarious matters he has raised with me
OL,18,Fin relation to this, and I will
OL,19,Frespond to him fully in due course."
OL,1,Woz5~k4{$z%~s1z5jw=hw1         G5/6
OL,2,W,.!+.!/*%/*%,.!/*%/*%/"-$T,,,,,,,,,,,,,
